riunif

DESCRIPTION

        Random indices of an object. (Reflexive uniform
        distribution).

USAGE

        riunif(x, n=1)

ARGUMENTS

        x       an object, typically a vector.

        n       Number of indices.

DETAILS

        The return should contain unique indices.

SEE ALSO

EXAMPLES

        x <- c(2, 3, 3, 4, 4, 5)
        riunif(x)
        riunif(x, 2)
